            "answer_text": "Can there be any translation of a literary work that does not in some way betray its original? Yes. Samuel Beckett - Wikipedia The Author himself translated much of his own work from English to French, or visa versa. You can\u2019t say the translator didn\u2019t understand what the author meant- in fact, it is quite hard to say which is the translation and which is the original or if those terms are even useful here\u2026 ",
